oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Photograph of group including Rosa Parks, Anne Braden, Carl Braden
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Group photograph of Civil Rights leader Rosa Parks at the home of activists Anne and Carl Braden

Rosa Parks, famous for helping organize the Montgomery Bus Boycotts in 1955-1956, attended a workshop led by Septima Clark at Highlander Folk School four months before refusing to give up her bus seat in Montgomery on December 1,1955. Photographs of Parks's time at Highlander were used in the propoganda campaign to shut the school down.
